# Obsidian Markdown

- Use frontmatter for new vault notes when metadata is useful.
- Use `[[wikilinks]]` for internal vault references.
- Use standard Markdown links only for external URLs.
- Prefer stable file names over cosmetic renames.
- Use clear headings and short callouts when highlighting disputes or open questions.
- For new wiki pages, link to related source notes, concepts, entities, or syntheses so graph and backlinks stay useful.
